      • equals

        public final boolean equals(Object o)
        Checks if the given object is equal to this object. The equals implementations for CompositeType may break the symmetry contract of the equals method.

        Why "may"? Because some implementations of Type checks if the compared object class is the same as the implementation

        This is because the types must be wrapped before invoking Object.equals(java.lang.Object) in any type
